name: Full Body Strength
description: A full-body strength workout for muscle building.
instructions: Perform 3 sets of push-ups (15 reps each set).
Follow with 3 sets of squats (20 reps each set).
Do 3 sets of pull-ups (10 reps each set).
Include lunges in 3 sets (12 reps each set).
Finish with a cool down and stretching exercises.
tips: Stay hydrated and maintain proper form during exercises.

name: Beginner Full Body Workout
description: A beginner-friendly full-body workout for general well-being.
instructions: Perform bodyweight exercises like squats, lunges, and push-ups.
Include core exercises such as planks and crunches.
Finish with a 5-minute cool-down and stretching.
tips: Focus on proper form and listen to your body. Gradually increase intensity as you become more comfortable.

name: Biceps and Triceps Builder
description: A beginner workout to build strength in biceps and triceps.
instructions: Perform bicep exercises like dumbbell curls (3 sets of 12 reps).
Include tricep exercises such as tricep dips (3 sets of 12 reps).
Finish with a 5-minute cool-down and stretching.
tips: Use light weights initially, focusing on proper form. Gradually increase intensity as you become more comfortable.
